Respect for all: We believe in treating everyone with respect, regardless of their race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, or any other personal characteristic.

Professionalism: We expect all employees to act professionally and to maintain a high standard of workmanship.

Communication: We encourage open and honest communication, and expect employees to communicate respectfully and constructively, even in difficult or stressful situations.

Confidentiality: We require all employees to maintain confidentiality in regards to the company's business practices, financial information, and any other confidential information.

Harassment-Free Workplace: We will not tolerate any form of harassment, bullying, or discrimination in the workplace.

Substance Abuse: We prohibit the use of illegal drugs and excessive use of alcohol while on the job or representing the company.

Ethical Conduct: We expect all employees to act in an ethical and responsible manner, in compliance with all relevant laws and regulations.

Conflicts of Interest: We expect employees to avoid conflicts of interest and to disclose any potential conflicts to their supervisor or the HR department.

Reporting Violations: Employees are encouraged to report any violations of this code of conduct to their supervisor or the HR department. All reports will be handled confidentially and investigated promptly.

Consequences: Employees who violate this code of conduct may be subject to disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment.
